        "authorId" : "a5bfe189-66bd-471c-a7d7-13abf7188474",
        "body" : "At present the tests don't run in Windows. This is because hyperspy imports matplotlib which defaults to the Qt backend that requires a screen. In unix it is possible to change the default matplotlib backend by just setting the MPLBACKEND environement variable but I don't think this is possible in Windows. I think that the matplotlib recipe workarounds this issue by patching matplotlib.",
        "createdAt" : "2017-06-20T11:41:04Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2017-06-20T11:41:04Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a5bfe189-66bd-471c-a7d7-13abf7188474",
        "tags" : [
